OL,5, Home Secretary James Cleverly has been 
OL,6, criticised for making a comment about  
OL,7, spiking his wife's drink at a Downing  
OL,8, Street reception.                      
OL,10,FHe reportedly said the ideal spouse is 
OL,11,F"someone who is always mildly sedated  
OL,12,Fso she can never realise there are     
OL,13,Fbetter men out there".                 
OL,15,FAccording to the Sunday Mirror, Mr     
OL,16,FCleverly also mentioned Rohypnol - a   
OL,17,Fso-called "date rape" drug.            
OL,19,FHe has apologised for making an "ironic
OL,20,Fjoke" in a private conversation.       
